Next, the nanoprobe was applied to detect CA125 in serum samples of patients with ovarian cancer. The samples obtained from Renmin Hospital of Wuhan University were also diluted by 100-fold for CA125 detection. The concentrations of CA125 in the three samples, respectively, which are all beyond above 35 U·mL−1. The CA125 concentrations in the serum of three patients were measured to be 160 U·mL−1
                        , 255 U·mL−1 and 315 U·mL−1, respectively, which are all beyond above 35 U·mL−1 and comparable to clinical values (Table 1
                        ). These results were further confirmed by standard addition experiments. The recoveries range from 98% to 102% with relative standard deviation (RSD) below 6%, which is satisfying for the quantitative assay of CA125 in biological samples.
